snippet.textDisplay:
Watching Lewis grow as a driver & person over the years has been a complete honour & absolute pleasure. People seem to forget he wasn't always as dominant as he is now, there were times when almost anything he did on track received penalties from the stewards. I personally believe this helped him mature & grow into the force he is now & his dominance is a direct result of those times. Huge respect has to go to anybody who can take those knocks & learn from them.
I remember watching Schumacher win his championships & claiming all his records, never did I think I'd be lucky enough to see another legend of the sport rise & surpass the achievements of the most successful driver of all time. I genuinely believed that nobody would ever come close, but here we are, on the brink of seeing that happen.
It's been so incredible to watch you rise over the last 12 years Lewis & I honestly feel blessed to have witnessed the 2 most successful drivers of all time (I'm also old enough to have watched the careers of senna & prost). Yes everyone has their favourite drivers past & present, but stats don't lie. I look forward to seeing you race over the next few years & watching you claim those final few records. Then there can be no doubters, you ARE the greatest of all time !!!
You're an inspiration & fantastic role model for present & future generations. Keep doing what you do & simply being you dude. Big love 💕

snippet.textDisplay:
This comment is for Lewis, I hope someone at Mercedes will show him this message.
Hi Lewis,
My name is Henry, I was born in 1997, and I have been a fan of f1 for as long as I can remember, but the first race I watched from start to finish was the Brazilian Grand Prix in 2008, when you won your first world championship. I remember being my 10 year old self, and saying to myself, that’s my favorite formula 1 driver of all time. Being just a kid, I never saw you as being different from the other drivers, I didn’t even have the capacity to think you were different because of your skin colour, I only saw you as just another British Formula 1 racing driver and now world champion.
Fast forward to the end of 2019 being almost 22 years old, I’ve sat down every Sunday since 2014 and have watched you win all of your five championships with Mercedes. You are the GOAT Lewis, I can’t wait to see you match and destroy Michael’s records. Like all the other f1 drivers, you are an f1 driver, you are not different from everyone else because of yours skin colour or where you have come from, or whatever some people might think. I guess the only difference between you and everyone else is that you are the greatest of all time.
Also if you’re down try anything, you have got to marlin fishing in Kona, Hawaii or Costa Rica. That is super fun! And if you’re up for a challenge that will test your will power and strength, marlin fishing where you could catch a 1000lb+ fish would be right up your alley.
Thanks Lewis, I hope this message gets to you. Merry Christmas!
Henry.

Being just a kid, I never saw you as being different from the other drivers, I didn’t even have the capacity to think you were different because of your skin colour, I only saw you as just another British Formula 1 racing driver and now world champion. 
Fast forward to the end of 2019 being almost 22 years old, I’ve sat down every Sunday since 2014 and have watched you win all of your five championships with Mercedes. You are the GOAT Lewis, I can’t wait to see you match and destroy Michael’s records. Like all the other f1 drivers, you are an f1 driver, you are not different from everyone else because of yours skin colour or where you have come from, or whatever some people might think. I guess the only difference between you and everyone else is that you are the greatest of all time. 
Also if you’re down try anything, you have got to marlin fishing in Kona, Hawaii or Costa Rica. That is super fun! And if you’re up for a challenge that will test your will power and strength, marlin fishing where you could catch a 1000lb+ fish would be right up your alley. 
Thanks Lewis, I hope this message gets to you. Merry Christmas! 
Henry.
